The following will report on the values for one platform. To run on multiple platforms, consolidate the data directories.

Step 1 - run benchmarks  
cd scripts
./collectNvprofData.sh <DIRECTORY_TO_PUT_DATA_IN> 
-- ie. ./collectNvprofData.sh ../data_run

Step 2 - consolidate benchmark data 
cd scripts 
./getPerformanceTimesAveraged.sh <DIRECTORY_DATA_PUT_IN_1> > <DATA_FILE_TO_PRINT_TO> or whatever text file, but the R plotting script needs to be updtaed as this is currently hardcoded)
-- ie. ./getPerformanceTimesAveraged.sh ../data_run > ../analysis/output.txt 


Step 3 - re-create plots 
cd analysis 
Rscript plotBenchmarkSpeedupMedian.R <benchmark of interest - { mm, cfd, spmv }>  <DATA_FILE_PRINTED_TO_IN_2>
-- ie. "Rscript  plotBenchmarkSpeedupMedian.R mm output.txt"

plots will be found in analysis/plots/<benchmark>_speedup.pdf
